<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.>
        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "Figure 1. Map showing the locus typicus (black star) of Paralaophontodes anjae sp. n. in Puente Quilo, Gulf of Quetalmahue, Chiloe Island, Chile." , "Figure 2. Paralaophontodes anjae sp. n., female. (A) habitus, dorsal view; (A ') dorsal process IX; (B) P 5; (C) genital field. Scale bars: (A) 100 µm; (A', B, C) 50 µm." , "Figure 5. Paralaophontodes anjae sp. n., female. (A) P 1, claw broken; (A ') P 1 enp- 2 of counterpart; (B) P 2 showing rudimental intercoxal sclerite; (C) P 3; (D) P 4. Scale bar: 50 µm." , "Figure 3. Paralaophontodes anjae sp. n., female. (A) A 1 and rostrum, arrow showing insertion of aes and accompanying setae of counterpart; (B) telson and FR, ventral view, Roman numerals indicating furcal setae. Scale bar: 50 µm." , "Figure 4. Paralaophontodes anjae sp. n., female. (A) A 2; (B) md; (B ') mandibular palp of counterpart; (C) mxl; (D) mx, proximal endite separated (arrow); (E) mxp. Scale bars: (A, E) 50 µm; (B, B' - D) 20 µm." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/127949" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/127950" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/127946" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/127947" , "https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/127948" .

